Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery vessel, the interior is slightly ribbed and bears traces of a grey-brown deposit, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and smudged remains of four lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393802) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393802)
